-- Ibovespa Futures Drop as Europe Outlook Adds to Global Concern
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2013-11-05T11:23:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-05/ibovespa-futures-drop-as-europe-outlook-adds-to-global-concern.html
Brazil ’s Ibovespa  futures  fell after
the European Union cut its growth outlook, rekindling concern
that the global recovery will falter.  Cia. de Bebidas das Americas , Latin America’s largest
brewer, may move after it was rated the equivalent of buy in new
coverage at Barclays Plc. Homebuilder  Even Construtora e
Incorporadora SA  may be active after posting third-quarter
earnings that exceeded analysts’ estimates.  Ibovespa futures contracts expiring in December fell 0.3
percent to 54,610 at 9:13 a.m. in  Sao Paulo . The real weakened
0.1 percent to 2.2495 per dollar. The Stoxx Europe 600 Index
lost 0.2 percent.  Gross domestic product in the 17-nation euro bloc will rise
1.1 percent in 2014, less than the 1.2 percent forecast in May,
the Brussels-based European Commission said today.  The Ibovespa entered a  bull market  Sept. 9 after rising 20
percent from this year’s low on July 3 through that day. The
gauge is still down 19 percent in dollar terms this year,
compared with a decline of 3 percent for the MSCI  Emerging
Markets  Index of 21 developing nations’ equities.  Trading volume of stocks in Sao Paulo was 6.06 billion
reais yesterday, compared with a daily average of 7.61 billion
reais this year through Oct. 22, according to the latest data
available from the exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
